node.text: I really appreciate all the people who have been coming out to show there support for my comeback. It means the world to me. I had a big phone call today that has flipped a switch in me. This belt right here was just the motivation I needed at this moment to remind me of what I’m capable of!

node.text: Let’s go live! Email me: TeamBuendiaCoaching@gmail.com

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Jeremy L. Buendia on August 17, 2021 tagging @yavalabs. May be an image of 1 person, biceps and beard.

node.text:
The goal is to be a little better everyday. Not allowing “off-days” to knock me off track. Consistent incremental progress adds up. 8 weeks ago, I didn’t look good enough to post a pic with my shirt off, and here I am today.
-
A lot can happen in a short time if you put your mind to it. Can’t wait to see what I’ll look like in another 8 weeks.
-
@yavalabs

node.text:
It’s always good to switch up your Pre-Workouts from time to time!
-
Next time you do, give @yavalabs PRE a shot!
-
I’ve been using it for 8 weeks straight & I’m loving it.
-
Very clean & effective pre workout. Beta-Alanine hits hard every time, & the pumps have been consistent!
-
Tag the stores you shop at so they know to pick up and carry @yavalabs in your area!

node.text:
#flexfriday
-
The best week of training I’ve had in a few years!
-
No better way to start my weekend than to take a scoop of @yavalabs PRE & catch a nasty arm pump!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jeremy L. Buendia on August 05, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, beard, biceps and people standing.

node.text:
8 weeks back. Up 20lbs. Finally enjoying my training again! It’s been a long long time!
-
I’m not 100% by any means but I’ve made a ton of progress and the pain has subsided greatly.
-
Big thank you to @getmegoings for doing tissue work on me 2-3x week consistently for the past 9 months. That combined with the recent physical therapy exercises has really made me some significant improvements. I’m still working on imbalances but they are much better than they were before.
-
I’m finally starting to move some decent weight (strength is still probably only at 70%) but my intensity and form has improved.
-
Just glad to be back doing what I love with a passion. Im going through a re-brand right now, but be ready for a new programs and a bunch of new content!
-
I want to thank everyone who’s supported me, and above all I want to give credit to Jesus Christ for being my savior and helping me stay above water during some tough times, without him I would have nothing & because of him I’m still going!
-
Staying in my own lane and trying pick up more momentum. 🙏🏽
